org.trimou.engine.context

Class ValueWrapper

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.trimou.engine.resource.AbstractReleaseCallbackContainer
      • org.trimou.engine.context.ValueWrapper
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ResolutionContext, ReleaseCallbackContainer

    @Internal
public final class ValueWrapper
extends AbstractReleaseCallbackContainer
implements ResolutionContext
    Wrapper for the resolved value object and release callbacks. It is not thread-safe. The AbstractReleaseCallbackContainer.release() method must be always called after the wrapper is used, even if the resolved object is null (there might be still some callbacks registered).
    Author:
    Martin Kouba
